    {\displaystyle {\tfrac {1}{P}}.}
   These samples can be deduced from one cycle of a periodic function 
  
    
      
        
          f
          
            P
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle f_{P}}
   which has Fourier series coefficients proportional to those samples by the Poisson summation formula:

  
    
      
        
          f
          
            P
          
        
        (
        x
        )
        ≜
        
          ∑
          
