          |
        
        f
        (
        x
        )
        
          
            |
          
          
            2
          
        
        
        d
        x
        =
        1.
      
    
    {\displaystyle \int _{-\infty }^{\infty }|f(x)|^{2}\,dx=1.}
  It follows from the Plancherel theorem that f̂(ξ) is also normalized.
The spread around x = 0 may be measured by the dispersion about zero defined by

  
    
      
        
